social_posts.post_text: Motivate. Motivate. Motivate. 2023, I’m ready for it. I started my fitness journey with the intention to shrink myself to be the size I thought I needed to be. Now, instead of making myself smaller, thinner & weaker, I’m able to own my power with strength, increased health and new capabilities. I’m very grateful for this journey and where it has brought me! Excited for the future & wants to come! 💛

2021 forced me to hustle and 2022 I did just that 🙏💛 Grateful for 2022, we’ll see what 2023 will bring to this model, host, actress, comedian, performer, TikToker, OF Creator, Gym Baddie 🥹🙏😘 

This year was filled with spiritual highs and lows, lessons and blessings, new beginnings and new connections. This year really helped me understand that I can have it all (with hard work & discipline) and not limit myself to only focus on one creative avenue.

Looking back I hadn’t realized I ventured out and tried so much! I had my first stand-up comedy special, shot & released my first lingerie campaign, co-hosted a talk show, an acting role specifically created to normalize a trans person’s experience, made music, walked Miami Swim Week, had a few viral videos on TikTok, performed on stage again after so long, AND had a mural painted in the Arts District in Miami during Art Basel. 🤯🤯

Thank you so much to all of my followers♥️🥹 y’all have been with me forever and I’d be nowhere without YOU!! ♥️

Thank you to God, my family, and to my community & the creators/artists who inspired me all this year 🏳️‍⚧️💛🥳💯 Have a blessed 2023! 🙌

Can I just say that squatting is not easy!! This is why I’m posting this video without any music or editing. Most people don’t bring up the fact that you absolutely need to have back muscles in order to support the weight of the bar and plates. The bar alone weighs 45 pounds, each of these plates weigh 10 pounds each. Not only is it nerve-racking to know that you have so much weight on your shoulders, but also the fear of embarrassing yourself in front of your peers at the gym is very real. I try to be conscious about how much weight I can handle and take my time, making my movements nice and controlled. As much as I want to add more weights, I know that I can possibly hurt myself by overloading and then not being able to get back up after I squat down. Building muscles should always be on a slow and progressive trajectory. 
I’m learning this the more I lift. 💕🍑🥵 but let me tell you I’m going to get this booty right though !!!!!!!
Slowly entering my muscle mami era 💯🏳️‍⚧️💘😌💪

Living the story Hollywood isn’t ready to tell ❤️ … or can’t seem to get right.

Dating in general is hard for anyone & adding other people’s bias plus bad experiences from the past doesn’t make it any easier. The media doesn’t help much and from the outside looking in, it can seem like our only options are to be overly sexualized, worship the devil, or having our trauma exploited for the sake of other peoples privileges. That doesn’t work for me.

There are other options for trans people besides what is being offered and represented in entertainment… maybe there is a reason why our positive and loving stories aren’t being told 🤷‍♀️. However, that’s not stopping us from living, loving and thriving in the light. 💯

I wasn’t given any positive examples of representation growing up but I’ve always known that the love I have in my heart was pure & worthy of existing. Being the change that people need to see in the world is both inspiring and terrifying at the same time. I’m happy I don’t have to do it alone. 

Never give up on love and most certainly never give up on the dream that you have for your life. It may never get easy, but it will always be worth it.

This might be a controversial post. Changing my body has not changed my connection to God. Many people see me as a role model, and I hope that my presence does inspire those individuals to conquer their obstacles and live their dreams. I’m not sharing this information to impose religious beliefs on anyone, I’m just sharing my own personal thoughts on my journey. Thank you so much ♥️ Also, as a child of God, I won’t let anyone get in my way of praising God or knowing Jesus. Again, like I stated in the video, we all have free will. I believe our relationship to God, his will, & how we choose to use our free will matters more than getting a tattoo, body piercing, BBL, or gender change. I fully embrace my entire life both before and after my transition. I’m still the same human being, same heart, same soul. I know that one day I will have to answer to a higher power and that is why I choose to use my time here to be grateful for everyday I wake up a healthy person and to help others to the best of my ability. 💕 my biggest hope is that people will open up their eyes and their hearts to come back to love ❤️

It’s insane how inspired I get when I take the time to venture out in the world and actually live. Not letting myself get so wrapped up in the separation between cis-normative spaces and LGBTQ+ safe spaces.

I always ask myself what good is a trans activist if you aren’t in these streets? If you don’t KNOW the people or can’t even relate to where they come from, what’s the point? Being a trans activist isn’t just about being a voice for the community or being famous for it. It’s also about LIVING life despite so many people wanting to take it away from you. It’s about being grounded and present in the world, taking up space, and radically creating a life for yourself that isn’t on the margins or outskirts of society where people don’t have to look at you. 

Visibility is key when you’re ready.

Know your value and remember you are worthy of living a healthy vibrant lifestyle too. Be brave enough to exist in a world that says you shouldn’t, confident enough to be your true self in any space, sharp enough to handle anyone’s ignorance and not let it affect you. ♥️ In the words of the great OG, @jlo, “Cuz I’m gonna live my life!” 🏳️‍⚧️ #letsgetloud ♥️

Miami swim week is currently on my mind. @iconswim 🖤

In full transparency, I always get in my head about my aesthetic during this time. The modeling industry is a business and it’s all about categorizing the correct body sizes according to representation and the brands imagine. I think about where my body fits in as a transwoman. Does it even really matter? Well, to me, yes. I want to be able to do my job to the best of my ability and that means keeping an eye on myself and the composition of my figure. Since the trans category is somewhat ambiguous, I often find myself becoming unsure of how I should present. I am also reminded of the trauma I experienced when I first started modeling, and I was told that I wasn’t enough, which was a pattern that was inherited from how the modeling industry treats women in general. I often find myself at the crossroads of living in my truth & doing what feels good for me and also wanting to be the best at what I do & what that means in the eyes of the bookers and the brands. Sure, I can rest in the novelty of being a tokenized trans person, but does it really even mean anything if my representation is not true to what exists in the outside world? I don’t only represent myself, I also represent other trans women, Latina women and women who have curves. 😋☺️☺️🙌🙌

Tomorrow is Pride Month and it seems like lately there has been more and more fear being brought up from underneath the carpet. Granted, we may never see a time when everyone is in agreement about this topic but honestly will the world ever truly be in agreement about every single thing? Probably not. 
 
As a transwoman I have privilege to never get harassed about my transness or denied access to public restrooms. However, I’m not opposed to having trans restrooms for the safety of everyone. We all deserve the right to pee in peace! As someone who has experience raising kids and who has had to create a kid safe narrative with all involved about my transition, I feel it’s not solely up to us to create kid safe narratives about LGBTQ+ people. It should be done respectfully and collectively. LGBTQ+ people are very visible, especially with everything happening in the media and on social media, so it’s foolish for parents to think they shouldn’t educate their children about who we are. 
 
The best thing we can do is try and really care about representing ourselves to the truest of our ability. There is no barrier between LGBTQ+ and straight people because at the end of the day, straight people birth us! We need to work together. This Pride season be diligent in protecting your peace and self worth. Practice patience & love with everything you do. Always remember to keep your integrity and grace. 
 
We are physics before we are biology. We are energy before we are even ourselves. 🫶

I moved to LA almost 5 years ago in hopes to become a better influencer and work in Hollywood more as an actor. Today, (with a little help) I cleared out the small space in Pasadena that I once kept & spending this time here, for the last time, has been both freeing and healing. I’m always going to own this city by the way, Pasadena is MINE. One can say that I looked at Los Angeles through rose colored goggles at first and during strict Covid lockdowns, all the protests, and all of the crime, the part of LA that I experienced was both awakening and very real. I even saw someone get stabbed from my apartment window. On a brighter note, I will never forget the beauty, nature and landscape. I will always remember the lessons I learned about protecting my authenticity and hustling like I never have before. I will always be grateful for it all because where I am now is because Los Angeles was so chaotic 🥹🙊. Pasadena was my saving grace, but still, everything I needed was so limited. I could never live with a scarcity mentality let alone live in literal scarcity. I need people. I need energy. I need vibrancy. I need culture. I am beholden for the authentic people in my life and nuance that I’m able to experience where I live now. 🫶

Self value & valuing your truth 💓 I found this video of me and @tellaeche talking about redefining the rules & breaking free of the expectations of the community. Most of us live on the border of taking up the space we deserve and knowing that some people that may never accept us. This pride I invite you to break free from the rules and ask yourself, what is the value in your truth? 🩷🩵🤍

Be gentle with yourself 🌸😊

Feeling this blond 💛 with pride month coming to a close and being aware of the writer’s strike in Hollywood, the terrible residuals for actors because of streaming (I’ve been on a few shows so I know), and the immense amount of anti-trans and anti-lgbt rhetoric and legislative efforts, it’s actually sad to say this Pride Month was not giving us what it could have. I want to remind everyone that we are in a battle and it’s definitely not a fair fight. We are constantly used to ignite fear in peoples heart and then used by some companies for the sake of diversity politics most often, too, for little to no compensation. Although some people might be happy with a picture in a magazine or a snip of their image in a commercial, our community needs way more. We deserve more than the distraction that is satisfying our ego. Talking about our experiences and digging deep into our stories becomes very soul sucking. Yet we are not fairly compensated nor even given the opportunity to accurately tell our stories in film/tv so that to inspire true and accurate narratives instead of the fear based narratives that clearly exist on a much larger scale. I feel grateful that I was able to partner with a company like AT&T this year 🙌 so grateful and privileged… They literally put on an entire tour for Pride. #turnupthelove However, it doesn’t feel right for me to just keep up with my image, ignoring the truth that I’m seeing. My career was built grass-roots directly from the community, before we had any platforms to where I am today. 15 years babe. I’d feel like a sellout if I didn’t speak on the truth. 

Now more than ever is when we must work together. We all have to come together and figure out the best way to make a more positive impact with the platforms that we have now. Should be less about each individual and more of what we can do as a collective and moving consciously through next years election, Pride 2024 & beyond. I am here and present, I hope you are too. ❤️

Changes were made. 💯

I am so grateful and more than happy to have been a voice for a change that so many people wanted to see in the world 🙏 You can’t get any more #pride than that! Period.

My babies 🦋 Monarch butterflies are an endangered species, & I feel so grateful to have been able to raise these babies on my own. I’ve learned a whole lot about raising them and watching the entire process was astonishing. One of the most surprising parts of this process was learning that caterpillars poop, a lot! Once I knew they were getting close to hatching, I kept them in a 4 foot enclosure so that they would have some time to fly around before I let them go. This is definitely something I would do again! 🤗 I hope they made tons of babies since all they listened to was perrero while they were in my apartment {insert twerk emoji}. I also hope they made it to Mexico for their migration. 🥹🦋 It was hard to let them go!

Progress 💯 there’s no sense in trying to please the world when you know you’re already blessed 😇 My life is the way I choose it to be, according to what I feel is right. As long as I have God on my side, I don’t need anyone’s approval. There’s way too much fear in the world and I refuse to internalize that. I will not be controlled by what I think others want from me, leaving myself and my free spirit on the back burner. It’s self sacrificing and disingenuous. It’s also fake AF. You know what life’s one & only guarantee is? Death… and you really think I want to spend life foolishly feeding my ego?  NOPE, it’s a trick. I choose to feed my soul !!! Society likes to put people in boxes and social media can create pressure on you to fit those boxes. So tell me this, what box is great enough to fit my unique self? I do not exist in just one paradigm. I’m gonna lift weights, I’m gonna walk fashion shows, I’m gonna praise God, I’m gonna be trans, I’m gonna be on tv, I’m gonna do drag shows, I’m gonna be a dog mom and I’m gonna raise butterflies 😊 Faith, community, wellness, family, love, work & wealth. Dassit, that’s my box. 🩷

Who doesn’t love dogs ? 🐶🐾 
It’s crazy how much dogs will change your life. When I first got my dogs I ugly cried 🥹. All I wanted to do was give them the best life and be the best dog mom ever. It was a lot of stress training 3 puppies at once and they really taught me so much about myself, unconditional love, and having structure. Whenever they got sick it was so dramatic for me, like a baby getting sick!! I remember the times I would run to the animal hospital for the simplest things ☺️☺️ Animals are truly a blessing and they are always communicating with you. It’s all in the eyes. You just have to be open enough to care ♥️🐾

First work out of 2024! Felt so good to be back! 💜🤍🤎 This is an example of a partial leg day. I also did a full cardio session after this workout. Full workout details, nutrition plan, and recovery program is available now! Link in bio 🔗💋

Back squats ‼️ some people squeeze at the top, some people don’t. I prefer to because I’m trying to lift my booty. Back squats are one of THE most important things to master when you’re on your fitness & weight training journey. It’s not about how heavy you can lift, it’s about what you can CONTROL first, in order to then get you to lift heavier. 

When I’m training my legs, I always like to include these even if I just warm up with the bar and add four 10lb weights. I know that this isn’t my max, but it’s definitely going to help me maintain my form and get some good tentiom so I don’t burn out and I can continue to finish the rest of my workout. 

The bar alone weighs 45 pounds, you can still get a great workout with just the bar. There’s no rush, and remember that building strength is an upward trajectory. Start with the basics, master them, and then focus on progressive overload.
